briefdescription.para: Requires two existing revolute or prismatic joints (any combination will work). The provided joints must attach a dynamic body to a static body.
Get the reaction force on body at the joint anchor in Newtons.
Get the reaction torque on the body at the joint anchor in N*m.

simplesect.para: returns true if the position errors are within tolerance.

briefdescription.para: A gear joint is used to connect two joints together. Either joint can be a revolute or prismatic joint. You specify a gear ratio to bind the motions together: coordinate1 + ratio * coordinate2 = ant The ratio can be negative or positive. If one joint is a revolute joint and the other joint is a prismatic joint, then the ratio will have units of length or units of 1/length.

detaileddescription.para: Warning: You have to manually destroy the gear joint if jointA or jointB is destroyed.
